The paper deals with lower bounds for testing properties of Boolean functions, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of adaptive and non-adaptive algorithms suggests that information theory (cs.IT) may also be relevant. The study of monotonicity is closely related to machine learning and statistics, which are covered by the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
